ADDITIONAL TERMS AND CONDITIONS

1. ETHICAL USE REQUIREMENT

   Users of this software must:
   
   a) Only use the software to analyze networks they own or have explicit 
      written permission to analyze.
   
   b) Comply with all applicable local, state, national, and international 
      laws and regulations.
   
   c) Not use the software for any malicious, unauthorized, or illegal 
      activities.

2. NO ACTIVE ATTACKS

   This software is designed for PASSIVE ANALYSIS ONLY. The software does 
   not and must not be modified to:
   
   a) Perform ARP spoofing or poisoning attacks
   b) Conduct man-in-the-middle attacks
   c) Send deauthentication frames
   d) Capture handshakes for password cracking
   e) Perform brute force or dictionary attacks
   f) Conduct WPS attacks
   g) Any other form of active network attack

3. DISCLAIMER OF LIABILITY FOR MISUSE

   The authors and contributors of this software shall not be held liable 
   for any damages, losses, or legal consequences arising from the misuse 
   of this software. Users assume all risks and responsibilities for their 
   use of the software.

4. EDUCATIONAL PURPOSE

   The simulation features included in this software are for EDUCATIONAL 
   PURPOSES ONLY and use synthetic data. They do not perform real attacks 
   and are intended to help users understand attack patterns for defensive 
   purposes.

5. DATA PRIVACY

   Users are responsible for ensuring that any data collected using this 
   software is handled in compliance with applicable privacy laws and 
   regulations, including but not limited to GDPR, CCPA, and other data 
   protection frameworks.
